FBIS4-21687 "jptnd009___94074" JPRS-TND-94-009 JPRS PROLIFERATION ISSUES 1 April 1994 INTERNATIONAL UN Security Council Statement on DPRK Inspections UN Security Council Statement on DPRK Inspections Tokyo Backs UNSC Stand OW0104032394 Tokyo KYODO in English 0258 GMT 1 Apr 94 OW0104032394 Tokyo KYODO English BFN [Text] Tokyo, April 1 KYODO -- Japan on Friday [1 April] supported a United Nations call on North Korea to allow full international inspection of its nuclear facilities suspected of being used to develop nuclear weapons. "The UN statement underlined what the international community wants North Korea to do to help resolve the issue of Pyongyang's suspected nuclear program through dialogue," Chief Cabinet Secretary Masayoshi Takemura told a news conference. "We will support this statement," the top government spokesman said. All 15 members of the UN Security Council, including China, a traditional ally of North Korea, agreed to issue the statement Thursday calling for Pyongyang to accept full inspections by the International Atomic Energy Agency.
